page.title: 12BASINGSTOKE CANAL:NATURE
page.content: The canal is not densely vegetated, but there are patches of rigid hornwort, waterlilies, bistorts and starwort.On the margins astilbe,iris, bur-reeds, cow parsley and purple loosestrife grow among nettles and grasses.The banks are lined with mixed trees, mainly oak, ash and beech but including hawthorn,holly,hazel,birch and willow.A wide variety of shrubs carpet the ground: blackberry,dogrose, honeysuckle,ivies,dogwood and guelder rose.Among the plants are cranesbill, herb robert,hypericum,plantain,wild arum,dog's mercury, ragwort, yarrow, vetches, creeping jenny, marestail and ferns.The animals observed were water voles and rabbits. Insects included water skaters, dragonflies and several varieties of butterfly. Moorhens were the only water birds seen.
